commitResults.messageTitle: Modify Find Command to accept financial plans and tags
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, the find command is rather limited in scope. It is only able
to search for names while a user might want to search by financial plans
or tags.

Let's:
- Expand the find command to search by tags and financial plans
  (substrings included)

We choose to search names by whole words because it is unlikely to
search for names by substrings, while tags and financial plans may have
substrings that make sense to search for.

Testing will be added in a future commit.

purpose anyway.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor CombinedPredicate to be more flexible
commitResults.messageBody:
CombinedPredicate only accepts one of
FinancialPlanContainsKeywordsPredicate, NameContainsKeywordsPredicate,
and TagContainsKeywordsPredicate each. This makes the usage of
CombinedPredicate difficult and inflexible. Using a common interface
with varargs will make the usage of CombinedPredicate easier and
more flexible.

Let's:
- Refactor the CombinedPredicate class
- Introduce a PersonContainsKeywordsPredicate interface to abstract the
  other predicate classes

A limitation to this current implementation would be that
CombinedPredicate is a bit of a misnomer, since it is an "or" predicate.
An "and" predicate of a similar nature would cause a naming clash.
However, we don't need such a predicate yet, so we'll stick to this
naming.
Also, there might be concerns about the ability of this
new CombinedPredicate to compare against other objects
of the same type. We don't need to
compare predicates by their actual functionality now,
so implementing a stronger equals() method can be done later.

sorting by lexicographical order, this has now been changes to "sort sort" to make
"sort" a default "help function" and "sort appointment" to be sorting by the appointment
time.

Currently, when scheduling an appointment with a person with an appointment
scheduled, the schedule command overrides the old appointment without
the users knowledge.

This fix keeps the implementation of this overriding appointment but adds a
prompt that lets users know the current appointment scheduled and asks the
user if he would like to override the appointment

This is done to enable schedule to have dual functionality of adding and
editting as well as a reminder of a potentially forgotten appointment with
a person and also as a quick way to override past appointments with a new
one.
